name: 1-[5-imino-4-(2-nitrophenyl)-4,5-dihydro-1,3,4-thiadiazol-2-yl]ethanone
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-724
Reason:
The basic unit for comparison is thiadiazole which has an estimated melting point range of 130-145 degrees Celsius. The additional functional groups will influence the melting point as follows:
- The ethanone unit (+C(=O)C) likely increases the melting point due to increased polarizability and stronger dipole-dipole interactions, estimated at a +20 increment.
- The phenyl ring attached to the nitro group both increases molecular complexity and contributes to intermolecular forces such as pi-pi interactions and dipole-dipole interactions (due to the nitro group). The phenyl ring might add +30 while the nitro group adds an estimated +25 due to its strong electron-withdrawing effect and the ability to form strong intermolecular hydrogen bonds.
- The imino group (=N-) can participate in hydrogen bonding and contributes to the rigidity of the molecule, which might add approximately +10.
Taking the midpoint of the thiadiazole melting point range as 137.5 C and adding the incremental values gives us the predicted melting point.
